{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"friendless-commonlaw-ragfish","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Problem\nThe default test suite writes synthetic plan-review/completion sidecars under T-1 and rec-0000 in the checkout live .tickets-tracker and leaves empty UUID ticket directories. These namespaces have no CREATE event, so the new one-pass PlanRelationSnapshot preload fails every real review with reducer-error before the LLM. Existing tracked synthetic events and empty directories require explicit recovery; strict snapshot failure must remain fail-closed for genuinely corrupt real ticket material.\n\n## Plan\n- Identify the exact tests/production boundary that resolves an omitted repo_root to the live checkout and reproduce each leak deterministically.\n- Add RED isolation coverage proving synthetic gate/verifier tests cannot change the live tracker HEAD or create directories there; use explicit temporary repositories or mocked event writers at the responsible test boundaries.\n- Preserve production event emission semantics; fix only test fixture isolation unless evidence identifies a production API bug.\n- Recover empty directories and tracked synthetic T-1/rec-0000 namespaces with a history-preserving tickets-branch commit and a recoverable quarantine, recording exact evidence.\n- Re-run focused tests, make check, the default suite, and review-plan 75de to prove the live store remains clean and the real review reaches its LLM gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Focused tests identify and reproduce every live-store writer responsible for T-1 and rec-0000 sidecars.\n- [ ] Synthetic plan-review and completion-verifier tests use explicit isolated stores or mocked event writers and do not mutate the checkout tracker.\n- [ ] The full default suite leaves the checkout tracker HEAD and directory set unchanged.\n- [ ] Production plan-review/completion sidecar emission remains covered and unchanged.\n- [ ] Strict relation snapshots still reject genuine reducer corruption; no fail-open skip is added.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Empty synthetic directories and tracked T-1/rec-0000 events are removed from the live tree through recoverable, history-preserving cleanup.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] review-plan 75de reaches the LLM gate after cleanup instead of returning reducer-error.\n","id":"d540-fdd1-318f-49a5","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":["test-isolation","plan-review","ticket-store"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Test verifier sidecars pollute the live ticket store"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784689134593021001,"uuid":"4fc7c280-4de5-4d91-a8dd-8eb0e4f1ae56"}